clusterList.phrase: sort of back in the day when surveyors ruled the battlefield the communicators never put us on the call sign lists the firing batteries all had call signs the supply guys had call signs forward observers infantry platoons even the chaplain's jeep driver all had their own assigned alpha-numeric code that changed every twelve hours or on command but not surveyors so we got tagged i was the man jones which evolved into tango mike juliet inside our battalion or echo four later five juliet for regimental traffic
